The syntax and function of the DROP verb is identical to that of the PUT verb.

> DROP

Drops an item you are holding in your hand onto the ground.

> DROP <thing>

Drops a specific <thing> you are holding in your hand onto the ground.

> DROP <thing> IN|ON|BEHIND|UNDER <container>

Puts a <thing> you are holding in your hand in a specific place (if it can be contained there).

